        <TD HEIGHT=141 COLSPAN=5>
        </TD>
        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-06-28 - Memorial Held for Miko on Povar</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> p>A memorial was held for Miko who passed away in the real world. Mika in the
real world was a US solder stationed in Bosnia, she was killed in an accident
last week. Mika was a level 42 monk, and a member of the XYZ guild on the Povar
server. The memorial was held Monday,&nbsp; June 26 2000, 6:00pm (PST) in the
Lake Rathe Arena and attended by over 115 players and several GMs. The memorial
was a touching event, with the GMs - all dressed in black- presenting tributes
to Miko and her exploits, along with poems and other tributes. </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: The Portal -  </font> <a href=http://www.portalnetgames.com </a> www.portalnetgames.com </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-06-28 - Gorden talks about PVP risk</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> I often get email from a few folks who make some very good arguments concerning
risk in PvP. Basically, the standpoint is that if the environment does not
contain risk, there is no sense in engaging in it. &quot;Item loot&quot; itself
does not handle this risk, as players of casting classes are not affected to the
same extreme as melee characters.
<p>One argument is that we should implement experience-loss in PvP. I like this
idea, unfortunately some core issues with the way life in EQ works makes
implementing this unreasonable. For anything that couldnt be handled in code, an
additional load would be placed on the CS staff. Believe it or not, even though
people playing on PvP servers should be more tolerant of interaction with other
players, 90% of the petitions there are for some kind of perceived harassment.
<p>The core EQ system, meaning, the things that define EQ as EQ, do not allow
some of these issues to be resolved without drastically changing the PvE portion
of the game which we want to remain intact.
<p>That said, I still firmly believe that some form of risk associated with PvP
needs to be in game. Since that risk cannot be experience-based, and item-based
risk doesnt hurt people who can bag their items or fight without them, Im
considering the following option: Making it so that everyone, regardless of
class, can only bind in cities on the PvP Servers only.
<p>City-only binding (again, on PvP servers only) would allow people to, for
instance, eject an opposing force from a zone, and provide the additional risk
of making all of them run back to recover their corpse and engage again.
<p>What are your thoughts on this? Do you feel that PvP needs more real and
equal risk associated with it regardless of class?
<p>-Gordon<br>
</p>

</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EverQuest Message Board -  </font> <a href=http://http://www.everquest.com </a> http://www.everquest.com </td></tr>    
